Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) on important accounts like Gmail, LinkedIn, and student portals.
Verify the sender’s email address before clicking any link.
Use encrypted cloud storage to store important project or research data.
Use strong and unique passwords for every account.
Keep your system and antivirus updated with regular software patches.
Report suspicious emails or cybercrime to the cybercrime portal or helpline (1930).
❌ Don’ts
Do not click on suspicious links in unknown emails.
Do not trust emails from unofficial domains like Gmail when they claim to be from organizations.
Do not share your username and password on unknown websites.
Do not use public Wi-Fi for sensitive tasks like banking or logging into important accounts.
Do not store sensitive files on unprotected USB drives.
Do not use simple passwords like your name, registration number, or birthdate.
